parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator assembly can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
warning messages on the dashboard such as "Check ABS"
"Check Brake System"
"Check VSC System"
and "Brake Malfunction".
